Narrator

Suddenly, the music began. It was "The Light in the Darkness," the same nationalist song that Lileas played during the congress vote.

Narrator

My term was almost over.

Narrator

It was the biggest gathering of people we'd managed to assemble during my campaign, and if my advisors were right, it was also the largest ever assembled in Soll Square.

Narrator

The noise of the crowd rose up around me on all sides. Would I ever address so many people again?

Narrator

Suddenly, the music began. It was "Vectern sis hirc," a famous patriotic song by the composer of the Sordish anthem. "Victory is here."

Narrator

Then Albin announced my name and invited me to the stage. It was finally time.

Narrator

Suddenly, the music began. It was "Vectern sis hirc," a famous patriotic song by the composer of the Sordish anthem. "Victory is here."

Narrator

Remus announced my name and invited me to the stage. It was finally time to give the campaign speech to endorse the National Front Party.

Narrator

Iosef announced my name and invited me to the stage. It was finally time.

Narrator

Albin gave me a nod and I stood up. In my dark gray suit and maroon tie, I walked up to the podium as the crowd started applauding.

Narrator

Around me, I saw a sea of Democrat Party banners and flags. It was as if people had painted the square yellow.

Narrator

Around me, I saw a sea of Liberal Party banners and flags. It was as if people had painted the square blue.
